The paper focuses on person re-identification using deep learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of robustness and accuracy in person re-identification, which is a concern in computer security (cs.CR) research.
